\id EPH - Akawaio New Testament Translation Project
\h E'PE'SAS
\toc1 Kareta Paarʉ Nennoko'pʉ E'pe'sas Pon Kon Ena'
\toc2 E'pe'sas
\toc3 E'pe'sas
\mt2 Kareta Paarʉ Nennoko'pʉ
\mt1 E'pe'sas Pon Kon
\mt2 Ena'
\imt1 Ekamanin
\ip \bk Kareta Paarʉ Nennoko'pʉ E'pe'sas Pon Kon Ena'\bk* esi isewankamasa' wapiya kuru, “Papa ekonekato' pɨ'…tanporo ikonekasa' amʉranʉ'to' pɨ' a'samʉtʉ ya', tanporon nɨ Epʉn pon mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ non pon, Kʉrai si itesa' pe” (1:10). Ipan pe Papa munkɨ amʉ' ekama'po pe rɨ nɨrɨ iyesi to' uko'manto' pe se ta e'kwa pe serɨ eke kuru Papa ekonekato' esi ta pe ka'pon amʉ' enato' pe tikin nɨ, tikin nɨ e'nɨto' poro Sises Kʉrai pokon pe.
\ip Wapiya iye'to' airɨ \bk E'pe'sas Pon Kon\bk* yau imenukanin uya emo'ka tʉusauro'to' ipɨ' tikin nɨ e'nɨto' ite'ma pɨ' tʉusaurokʉ winɨ Papa ikʉipʉnʉ uya tʉmunkɨ ton anʉnsa', to' pɨ' isentu'masa' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ to' mo'kasa' iya to' makooi apai Sises Kʉrai tʉmu poro, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ eke kuru Papa usauro'sa' rʉ'pʉ e'ma takan pe iye'ku'sa' Wakʉ A'kwarʉ winɨ. Ipɨkɨron pe iyesi airɨ ipan pe tʉnmenuka'pʉ ennin nan ekama'po iya to' uko'manto' pe tikin nɨ to' e'to' Kʉrai yau enato' ipɨkɨrɨ pe i'nai rɨ to' uko'manto' yau a'samʉtʉ pe.
\ip Tu'kan nɨ panton i'tuto' yai main utapurɨsa' tikin nɨ Papa munkɨ amʉ' esi enpoikanin pe tikin nɨ Kʉrai yau to' e'to': So'si esi pun esa' kasa, Kʉrai i'pai pe; mɨrɨ pe pʉra ɨutɨ tamɨsen kasa, Kʉrai itekun airo'nan tɨ' pe; mɨrɨ pe pʉra no'pʉ kasa, Kʉrai itaan'pʉ pe. Serɨ imenukasa' kareta enuku ipan pe rɨ ka'ta' ekamato' ya' imenukanin utɨ koro'tau eke rɨ wakʉ nonkasa' Papa uya winɨ usenuminkan nɨto' Kʉrai poro. Tanporon nɨ usene Kʉrai usi'nʉnkato' weyu yau, use'man nɨto', usentu'man nɨto', eke rɨ wakʉ nonkasa' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ esuken ɨri pʉra e'nɨto'.
\iot Iyawon Ekamanin
\io1 Ekamanin (1:1-2)
\io1 Kʉrai mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ so'si (1:3—3:21)
\io1 Emenna' pe uko'man nɨto' Kʉrai yau (4:1—6:20)
\io1 Iu'matʉ (6:21-24)
\c 1
\p 
\v 1 Paarʉ, Kʉrai Sises nennoko'pʉ itekare ekamai' Papa eseru winɨ, winɨpaino,\x - \xo 1:1 \xt Inkupʉ'pʉ 18:19-21; 19:1\x*
\p Wakʉ ton E'pe'sas pon kon\f + \fr 1:1 \ft Tʉron nɨ imenukasa' ton yau, \fq E'pe'sas pon kon \ft pʉra iyesi.\f* enakan, tʉusaurokʉ'pʉ awɨron kon\f + \fr 1:1 \fq tʉusaurokʉ'pʉ awɨron kon; \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra, \fq apurɨnin nan\f* Kʉrai Sises yau:
\p 
\v 2 Wakʉ nʉnonkasa' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉusewankamai' pʉra e'nɨto' nesii ɨyenakan kon pe Papa, ukʉipʉnʉ kon mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Itepuru Sises Kʉrai winon.
\s1 Iya'kwarʉ Pe Pʉreman Nɨto' Kʉrai Yau
\p 
\v 3 Apurɨpɨ'to' nesii Papa mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ uyepuru kon Sises Kʉrai kʉipʉnʉ iwano' pe, wakʉ pe upʉremanin nʉ'pʉ kon tanporon nɨ iya'kwarʉ pe pʉreman nɨto' Epʉn po e'nɨ pata yau Kʉrai yau.
\v 4 Apʉne pʉra uyanʉnsa' iya 'nokon pɨ' pata ekoneka rawɨrɨ wakʉ pe te'san pe mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨri pe pʉra tenu yau. Tʉusi'nʉnkato' yau
\v 5 tʉmunkɨ pe e'nɨto' yau ku'nɨ'pʉ iya pena\f + \fr 1:5 \fq tenu yau. Tʉusi'nʉnkato' yau tʉmunkɨ pe e'nɨto' yau ku'nɨ'pʉ iya pena; \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra, \fq tenu yau tʉusi'nʉnkato' yau. Tʉmunkɨ pe e'nɨto' yau ku'nɨ'pʉ iya pena.\f* Sises Kʉrai poro, pori' pe te'to' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ teseru awɨrɨ.
\v 6 Ikuu'pʉ iya tapurɨpɨ'to' pe, wakʉ nonkasa' tʉuya pɨ', i'nʉmʉra rɨ Tʉmu tʉni'nʉnkanʉ yau.
\v 7 Iyau e'man nɨto' esi imʉnʉ poro, makoi pɨ' usentu'man nɨto', Papa uya wakʉ nonkasa' na'ne' awɨrɨ eke pe kuru rɨ\x - \xo 1:7 \xt Koro'se 1:14\x*
\v 8 upona'nokon itʉsa' iya eke pe kuru rɨ tanporo tʉpu'ketʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ito'ka'nʉ'to' pokon pe.
\v 9 Mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ama'ai tʉnkupʉnʉ teseru pori' pe te'to' awɨrɨ koneka'pʉ iya i'tuto' kon pe, te'kuu'pʉ rʉ'pʉ Kʉrai yau.
\v 10 Serɨ ekonekan nɨsa' e'ku'to' pe ita'ku'tɨto' weyu ton e'seposa' a'tai—tanporon nɨ Epʉn pon mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ non pon amʉranʉ'nin pe tikin nɨ itesa', kʉrɨ rɨ kʉrɨ rɨ Kʉrai.
\p 
\v 11 Kʉrɨ rɨ yau rɨ nɨrɨ utanʉn nɨ'pʉ'nokon pena,\f + \fr 1:11 \fq utanʉn nɨ'pʉ'nokon pena; \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra, \fq eponin pe enan nɨ'pʉ'nokon pena\f* inkuu'pʉ iye'ku'to' pe awɨrɨ rɨ tanporon nɨ tʉrawasomanin mɨrɨ kasa iye'to' pe tawon teseru awɨrɨ,
\v 12 ina, wapiya Kʉrai yau te'ku'to' ke iye'sa' kon, e'to' pe eke pe iku'to' apurɨpɨ'to' ku'nin pe.
\v 13 Mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨmɨrɨ'nokon nɨ nɨrɨ esi'pʉ Kʉrai yau i'nairon maimu etasa' auya'nokon a'tai, wakʉ ɨyepika'tɨto' kon ekareei. Apurɨsa' auya'nokon a'tai, ama'kʉi'tɨ'pʉ kon a'si'to' ike ke, usauro'nɨsa' rʉ'pʉ ipɨ' Wakʉ A'kwarʉ,
\v 14 itʉsa' uneporonʉ kon ekamanin pe kamoro Papa iwano' pe te'san e'ma pona rɨ—eke pe tesi pɨ' tapurɨpɨ'to' pe.
\s1 Tenki Tapɨtʉ Mɨrɨ Awonsi'kɨ Ɨpʉreman
\p 
\v 15 Serɨ wenai, Itepuru Sises apurɨto' auya'nokon eta'pʉ uya si'kɨrɨ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ wakʉ ton i'nʉnkato' auya'nokon,
\v 16 ereutasa' pʉra rɨ iyesi ɨpɨ'nokon tenki tapɨtʉ pɨ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨpona'nokon ɨpʉremato' rɨ esi uyenu yau.
\v 17 Urɨ'nokon epuru Sises Kʉrai e'to' itese' pɨ' Papa, meruntɨ pe te'sen Ikʉipʉnʉ, ekama'po pɨ' rɨ esi ɨrepato' kon pe iya pu'ketʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ enpoikanin A'kwarʉ ke,\f + \fr 1:17 \fq A'kwarʉ ke; \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra, \fq a'kwarʉ ke\f* wakʉ pe parɨ i'tunin pe ɨwesi kon pa.
\v 18 Ɨpʉrema rɨ nɨrɨ ɨyewan kon yau ɨyenu kon uta'kwakato' pe ɨkɨ'mato' iya 'nokon ipona ɨye'ku'to' kon i'tunin pe ɨwesi kon pa, eke pe kuru rɨ meruntɨ pe ɨneporonʉ kon esi wakʉ pe te'san yau,
\v 19 mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ mɨrɨ kaisaron ta pokena' pen nɨ urɨ'nokon apurɨnin nan iwano' pe intʉrʉnʉ eke kuru rɨ ipana'pano. Mɨrɨ ipana'pano esi eke imeruntɨrʉ e'tʉrawasoma pe rɨ,
\v 20 inapurɨ'pʉ Kʉrai yau i'mʉ'sa'ka'pʉ iya a'tai iyerikʉ'pʉ apai, mɨrɨpan aponontɨ tʉuya a'tai temiyatʉ enwo'netʉ winɨ Epʉn po e'nɨ pata yau;\x - \xo 1:20 \xt Eren 110:1\x*
\v 21 ɨnnɨ rɨ tanporon nɨ esa' wannɨ pe te'sen mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ eke ton, pana'pano mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ eke pata esanon, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tanporon eke pe te'sen ese' ese'tɨn nɨto', serɨ a'taino rɨken pen e'tane serɨ entakan pe rɨ te'sen a'taino entaino.
\v 22 Mɨrɨpan Papa uya tanporon nɨ tʉsa' i'ta o'koi' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ anʉnsa' iya tanporon nɨ i'pai pe iye'to' pe so'si iwano' pe,\x - \xo 1:22 \xt Eren 8:6\x*
\v 23 ipun pe si te'sen, kʉrɨ rɨ pe rɨ si tanporon nɨ arʉ'tɨnin tanporon winɨ rɨ.\x - \xo 1:23 \xt Koro'se 1:18\x*
\c 2
\s1 Nurɨne Iyenasa' Kʉrai Yau
\p 
\v 1 Ɨmɨrɨ'nokon si, iyeri'sa' pe iye'sa' rʉ'san main yawɨrɨ pʉra mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ amakooi kon yau,\x - \xo 2:1 \xt Koro'se 2:13\x*
\v 2 ɨuko'mamʉ'pʉ kon na'ne' iyau serɨ orʉ eseru awɨrɨ ɨwesi kon a'tai, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ka'yawon kon esanon, iya'kwarʉ e'tʉrawasoman pɨ' na'ne' kamoro main awɨron kon pen yau.
\v 3 Tanporo e'nɨ na'ne' kaisa rɨ uko'man nɨ'pʉ'nokon to' koro'tau pena a'tai, u'naino kon umakooi kon e'to' i'se kupʉ pɨ'\f + \fr 2:3 \fq umakooi kon e'to' i'se kupʉ pɨ'; \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra, \fq upun kon pɨ'\f* mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ i'se iye'to' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ isenuminkato' pɨkɨrɨ utɨn pɨ'. To' kasa rɨ, i'naino kota'man nɨto' iwano' pe e'nɨ'pʉ.
\v 4 E'tane apʉne pʉra eke pe ui'nʉnkato' kon iya esi wenai, Papa, eke pe rɨ isentu'mato' te'sen,
\v 5 uya nurɨne uku'sa' kon Kʉrai pokon pe iyeri'sa' pe rɨ e'nɨ tane main awɨrɨ pʉra e'nɨto' yau. I'nai rɨ kuru iyesi, eke wakʉ nonkasa' winɨ ɨyepika'tɨsa' kon.
\v 6 Mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Papa uya ui'mʉ'sa'kasa' kon Kʉrai pokon pe, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ uyaponontɨsa' iya 'nokon ipokon pe Epʉn pe te'sen pata yau, Kʉrai Sises yau,
\v 7 enpoikato' tʉuya serɨ entakan nʉye'ai'ne' a'tai mɨrɨ kaisaron ta pokena' pen wakʉ nonkasa', enpoikasa' iya ɨsi'nʉnke' pe te'to' yau upɨ'nokon Kʉrai Sises yau.
\v 8 Apʉne pʉra wakʉ nonkasa' winɨ ɨyepika'tɨsa' kon, apurɨto' poro—mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ serɨ esi ɨwinon kon pen, Papa nʉtʉrʉnʉ mɨrɨ—
\v 9 tʉrawaso pɨkɨron pen, ɨnʉ' rɨ utapurɨ namai'.
\v 10 Apʉne pʉra Papa tʉrawasooi rʉ'san urɨ'nokon, ika'sa' kon Kʉrai Sises yau wakʉ tʉrawaso ku'nin nan pe, Papa nʉkoneka'pʉ uye'mata'nokon iku'to' pe.
\s1 Kʉrai Yau Tikin Nɨ Enan Nɨsa'
\p 
\v 11 Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨ', ɨyenu kon yau iku'tɨ' Esuwerʉ amʉ' pe pʉra ɨwesi'pʉ kon ɨyentusa' kon winɨ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ, “itun pi'pɨ iputurʉkasa' kon pen” tukai' ɨyesakʉ'pʉ kon, “itun pi'pɨ iputurʉkasa' kon” tukai' tʉusesa'san uya (ka'pon amʉ' nʉkupʉnʉ tʉpun kon pɨ' temiyatʉ kon ke)—
\v 12 ɨyenu kon yau mɨrɨ iku'tɨ', mɨrɨ a'tai Kʉrai piyapai iyemo'kasa' pe ɨwesi'pʉ kon, Esuwerʉ yawon kon pe pʉra mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨnnon kon pe rɨ ekonekan nɨto' pɨ' usauro'nɨto' piyapai, iye'ku'to' pʉra rɨ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Papa pʉra rɨ serɨ non po.
\v 13 E'tane si serɨ pe Kʉrai Sises yau ɨmɨrɨ'nokon, pena ɨnnɨ iye'sa' kon ne'sa' si a'ko pe Kʉrai mʉnʉ poro.
\p 
\v 14 Apʉne pʉra kʉrɨ rɨ rɨ esi usewankaman namai'no pe, asa'rɨ te'san ku'nin nʉ'pʉ tikin nɨ, mɨrɨpan uya wa'kʉ'nin pe te'sen ma'tanʉkʉ'pʉ, ɨ'seyaton pe e'nɨto' wekupiri,
\v 15 tʉpun winɨ main, Mosi' winon nonka'pʉ tʉuya winɨ apiyontɨn nɨto' iya mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ iyawɨrɨ e'nɨto' ton pokon pe. Ika'to' pe tʉuya iye'ku'to' esi'pʉ tikin nan pe asa'ron apai, usewankaman pʉra si iyesi tʉku'se;\x - \xo 2:15 \xt Koro'se 2:14 \x*
\v 16 mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ serɨ si tikin nan ipun yau to' konekanin pe asa'rɨ rɨ marɨ Papa piya' kurusu' po terikʉ winɨ, to' usewa'nomato' mo'ka'pʉ iya.\x - \xo 2:16 \xt Koro'se 1:20 \x*
\v 17 Iyee'pʉ mɨrɨpan uya tʉusewankamai' pʉra e'nɨto' ekama'pʉ ɨmɨrɨ'nokon ɨnnɨ te'san pɨ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ a'ko pan kon nʉ'san pɨ'.\x - \xo 2:17 \xt Aisaya 57:19 \x*
\v 18 Apʉne pʉra iporo asa'rɨ rɨ marɨ urɨ'nokon utɨto' e'ma esi Ikʉipʉnʉ piya' tikin nan Iya'kwarʉ winɨ.
\p 
\v 19 Mɨrɨ epe'pʉ pe, ɨnnon kon pe pʉra mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ sunwaron kon pe pʉra ɨwesi kon, e'tane Papa munkɨ amʉ' tonpa pe mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ itiwʉ' tau te'san tonpa ye' ton pe,
\v 20 itamɨsa' pe iyapon pe te'san itekare ekamai' enno'sa' kon mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ pu'kena' amʉ' po, kʉrɨ rɨ rɨ nin si Kʉrai Sises itekun airon eke tɨ' pe.
\v 21 Kʉrɨ rɨ yau tanporo mɨrɨ amɨsa' enasa' ɨsipona, mɨrɨpan nin si e'mʉ'sa'kasa' wakʉ use'man nɨto' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨpʉreman nɨto' iwʉ' pe tenai' Itepuru yau.
\v 22 Mɨrɨpan yau nin si ɨmɨrɨ'nokon nɨ nɨrɨ utamɨsa' mɨrɨ a'samʉtʉ yau itiwʉ' pe ɨyena kon pa Papa uko'manto' yau pe Ta'kwarʉ winɨ.
\c 3
\s1 Paarʉ, Esuwerʉ Amʉ' Pen Pɨ' Itekare Ekamanin
\p 
\v 1 Mɨrɨ wenai, urɨ, Paarʉ, Kʉrai Sises iwano' pe a'sisa' pe te'sen ɨmɨrɨ'nokon Esuwerʉ amʉ' pen iwano' pe—
\p 
\v 2 Eta'pʉ auya'nokon kuru rɨ Papa uya wakʉ nonkasa' tʉrawasooi, iye'tʉsa' uyena', ɨyena'nokon mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉron kon ena' ekanto' pe uya ɨpika'tɨnin kon pe.
\v 3 Serɨ tonan tawon usenpoika'pʉ uyena', to'ken nʉ'kwɨ imenukaka'sa' uya na'ne' ipɨ'.
\v 4 Mɨrɨ ene auya'nokon a'tai, ito'ka'nʉkʉ auya'nokon Kʉrai nʉkupʉnʉ tonan tau ennin pe esi,
\v 5 ka'pon amʉ' uya i'tuto' pe iye'sa' rʉ'pʉ pen tʉron nɨ a'tai iye'sa' kon ena' serɨ a'tai isenpoikasa' na'ne' kasa Iya'kwarʉ winɨ wakʉ ton Papa nennoko'san itekare ekamai' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ pu'kena' amʉ' ena'.
\v 6 Serɨ tonan tawon, wakʉ itekare poro Esuwerʉ amʉ' pen esi Esuwerʉ amʉ' pokon pe ɨsi'kaisa rɨ itesa' pe te'ton kon pe, tikin nan nɨ ipun pʉ'kʉ pe ɨsi'kaisa rɨ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨsi'kaisa rɨ ikupʉ tukai' usauro'nɨsa' eponin nan pe Kʉrai Sises yau.\x - \xo 3:6 \xt Koro'se 1:26-27 \x*
\p 
\v 7 Serɨ itekare poitorʉ pe iyenasa' rʉ'pʉ urɨ Papa uya wakʉ nonkasa' ke urepasa' pɨ' tʉpana'pano e'tʉrawasoma poro.
\v 8 Se pe rɨ e'tane sepan kon kuru nɨrɨ Papa munkɨ amʉ' o'koi' kuru, serɨ wakʉ nonkasa' ke urepa'pʉ: Esuwerʉ amʉ' ton pen ena' iwarinpa pokena' pen nɨ eke Kʉrai iwano' ekamanin pe.
\v 9 Uyanʉmʉ'pʉ tonan tau Papa, tanporon konekanin nʉ'pʉ, nʉkuu'pʉ iyepiya'tɨ si'kɨrɨ ku'nin pe sa'man pe pʉra tanporon kon ena'.
\v 10 Iteseru esi'pʉ serɨ pe si, so'si poro, i'tu pokena' pen nɨ Papa pu'ketʉ enato' pe ti'tusen pe esa' wannɨ ton mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ eke ton ena' Epʉn eseru pe te'sen yawon kon,
\v 11 inkero' rɨ mɨrɨto' pe ta'pʉ iya rʉ'pʉ inenuka'nʉkʉ'pʉ Kʉrai Sises, uyepuru kon yau.
\v 12 Iyau mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ apurɨto' uya'nokon poro Papa epoto' pe iteme'nin pʉra mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ en wannɨ yau te'se.
\v 13 Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨ', ɨyekama'po uya 'nokon, temiya'nʉnse pʉra ɨwesi kon pa, ɨwenai'nokon ekota'ma pɨ', eke pe ɨku'to' kon ipɨ' pɨ' rɨ.
\s1 E'pe'sas Pon Kon Pona Ɨpʉreman Nɨto'
\p 
\v 14 Mɨrɨ wenai Ikʉipʉnʉ rau e'sekunka,
\v 15 Ikʉipʉnʉ tanporon kon a'samʉtʉ yawon kon apurɨnin nan Epʉn mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ non pon kon uya tese' kon eposa' na'ne' iwinɨ.
\v 16 Ɨpʉrema eke pe rɨ te'sen eke pe tʉku'to' apai ɨmeruntɨtanʉ'to' kon pe iya tʉpana'pano ke Ta'kwarʉ poro ayau'nokon,
\v 17 mɨrɨ kasa si, Kʉrai e'to' pe ayau'nokon apurɨto' poro. Mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨpʉrema kanan ɨmɨrɨ'nokon, imisitasa' pe mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ iyekonekasa' pe ɨwesi kon pa usi'nʉnkan nɨto' yau,
\v 18 tʉpana'pano ke ɨwesi kon pa, wakʉ ton amʉtʉ pe, ito'ka'nʉ'nin nan pe eke pe rɨ ika'ta, kusan pe rɨ, ka'tau rɨ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ i'nau rɨ Kʉrai usi'nʉnkato' esi,
\v 19 mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ i'tu kon pa serɨ usi'nʉnkan nɨto', i'tunin pe e'nɨto' entaino rɨ—autarʉ'tɨ kon pa eke pe kuru Papa uya ɨrepato' kon ike ke.
\p 
\v 20 Serɨ si ipona iku'nin pe te'sen ipʉ'kʉ i'tu pʉra rɨ ekama'posa' entai rɨ mɨrɨ kasa na'kɨ tato' entai rɨ, tʉmeruntɨrʉ awɨrɨ ne'tʉrawasomayai'ne' uyau'nokon,
\v 21 iwano' pe eke pe iku'to' nesii, so'si tau mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Kʉrai Sises yau siyaro' kon poro rɨ, tɨwɨrɨ rɨ, tɨwɨrɨ rɨ! Amen.
\c 4
\s1 Tikin Nɨ E'nɨto' Kʉrai Pun Yau
\p 
\v 1 A'sisa' pe Itepuru iwano' pe esi koro'tau, ipan pe ayapiyo'ma uya 'nokon ɨuko'mamʉ kon pa uko'man nɨto' yau ikɨ'masa' kon pe te'san pe anʉnsa' auya'nokon na'ne' yau.
\v 2 Mɨ pe te'ku'san pe pʉra kuru e'tɨ', ɨ'sɨ'mʉn yaino kon pe e'tɨ'; tʉuseta'kasan pe pʉra, ɨusi'nʉnka kon pɨ' ɨtonpa kon tʉpika'tɨi' e'tɨ'.\x - \xo 4:2 \xt Koro'se 3:12-13 \x*
\v 3 Tikin nɨ ɨwe'to' kon Iya'kwarʉ iwano' yau enkurunpatɨ' kuru tʉusewankamai' pʉra e'nɨto' na'si'ai'ne' poro.
\v 4 Moro tikin nan ipun esi mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tikin nan Iya'kwarʉ—ɨkɨ'masa' kon na'ne' kasa kuru tikin nan ɨye'ku'to' kon ya' ɨkɨ'masa' kon a'tai—
\v 5 tikin nan Itepuru, tikin nan apurɨto', tikin nan epa'taisiman nɨto';
\v 6 tikin nan Papa, tanporon kon kʉipʉnʉ, tanporon entaino, tanporon poron nɨ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tanporon yawon nɨ.
\p 
\v 7 E'tane uiwano' kon pe e'nɨ na'ne' kaisa rɨ wakʉ nonkasa' e'tʉsa' upona'nokon Kʉrai uya iku'sa' na'ne' awɨrɨ.
\v 8 Mɨrɨ wenai ta iya:\f + \fr 4:8 \fq ta iya; \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra, \fq ta Papa uya\f*
\q1 “Iyenu'sa' a'tai ka'ta',
\q2 a'sisa' kon arɨ'pʉ iya ta'kɨrɨ,
\q2 mɨrɨpan uya repan nɨto' tʉsa' ka'pon amʉ' ena',”\f + \fr 4:8 \ft Eren 68:18\f*
\m ta iya.
\v 9 (Ɨ'rɨ ta e'kwa pe “Iyenu'sa'” ta? Iu'tɨ'pʉ pe rɨ marɨ iyesi non pona, non pe te'sen ya'.\f + \fr 4:9 \fq non pona, non pe te'sen ya'; \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra, \fq non o'no, non pe te'sen ya'\f*
\v 10 Kʉrɨ rɨ iu'tɨsa' rʉ'pʉ rɨ kʉrɨ rɨ iyenu'sa' rʉ'pʉ ka'ta' rɨ ka' enta' rɨ, tanporon nɨ mɨ yawɨron yau te'to' pe.)
\v 11 Kʉrɨ rɨ uya tʉron kon kuu'pʉ itekare ekamai' enno'sa' kon pe, tʉron kon pu'kena' amʉ' pe, tʉron kon itekare ekamanin nan pe, tʉron kon ka'pon amʉ' ennin nan pe mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ti'sa amʉ' pe,
\v 12 Papa munkɨ amʉ' konekanin nan pe tʉrawaso ku'nin nan pe, Kʉrai pun e'ka'to' pe,
\v 13 tikin nɨ enan pʉ'kʉ pona apurɨto' yau mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Papa Mumu i'tuto' yau mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ wakʉ pe iyakʉ'pʉsa' pe, Kʉrai yau eke pe utarʉ'tɨn nɨto' wakʉ ke eponin pe.
\p 
\v 14 Mɨrɨ a'tai mʉre' e'nɨ'nokon pen mɨrɨ, sipa'sipa nʉna'popɨtʉnʉ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ se airɨ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ mɨ airɨ ka'pon amʉ' uya enupan winɨ ennakanin nan a'setunʉ uya apɨ' nɨ enku'tɨnin teseru kon ke pen.
\v 15 E'tane ru'ku, usi'nʉnkan yau i'nairon pɨ' tʉusauro'sen pe, tanporon yau usemo'ka'nokon u'pai kon pe te'sen, Kʉrai kaisa rɨ.
\v 16 Iwinɨ tanporo ipun ena ɨsipona ikara ton ke, usemo'ka e'kapʉ tiwano' pe usi'nʉnkato' yau, ɨsi'kaisa rɨ tʉtʉrawasooi kon kupʉ to' uya ke.\x - \xo 4:16 \xt Koro'se 2:19\x*
\s1 Uko'man Nɨ Iweyu Munkɨ Pe
\p 
\v 17 Serɨ ta uya nin si ɨpɨ'nokon, ta uya kuru rɨ Itepuru yau ɨpɨ'nokon, kɨko'mantʉu serɨ enta' itekare apurɨnin nan pen, iwotori'pɨ pʉra tʉusenuminkato' kon yau te'san kasa.
\v 18 To' ewarumansa' ito'ka'nʉ'to' tʉuya'nokon yau, mɨrɨpan kon e'ta'nʉ'sa' Papa iwano' uko'man nɨto' piyapai, apʉne pʉra to' yau na'ne' ito'ka'nʉ'nin pen esi to' ewan usa'manta winɨ.
\v 19 To' ewan enasa' sa'man pe, to' rɨ e'tʉsa' ɨri ku'to' pe tʉuya'nokon ipan pe rɨ tʉuse'se'tɨto' kon nɨ tʉnonkai', mɨrɨpan kon uya ti'tui' pʉra rɨ ɨri ton kupʉ.
\p 
\v 20 Ɨmɨrɨ'nokon, mɨrɨ kasa Kʉrai i'tunin pe ɨyena'pʉ kon pen.
\v 21 I'nai rɨ eta'pʉ auya'nokon mɨrɨpan pɨ' ɨusenupa'pʉ kon i'nairon Sises yau na'ne' awɨrɨ.
\v 22 Ɨyenupa'pʉ kon, ɨuko'mamʉ'pʉ kon eseru pɨ', penaro' ɨyeseru kon nonka kon pa, ɨyenku'tɨpai'nokon te'sen pɨkɨrɨ ɨwesi kon nʉma'tanʉkʉ'pʉ;\x - \xo 4:22 \xt Koro'se 3:9 \x*
\v 23 emenna' pe ɨyenato' kon pe ɨusenuminkato' kon yau;
\v 24 emenna' ɨyeseru kon ya' ɨyena kon pa, iye'ka'sa' rʉ'pʉ Papa kasa iye'to' pe i'nairon ipoken e'nɨto' yau mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ wakʉ pe e'nɨto' yau.\x - \xo 4:24 \xt Iseneses 1:26; Koro'se 3:10\x*
\p 
\v 25 Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨ', akaisarɨ'nokon kasi ye' pe te'sen inonkatɨ', mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ i'nairon pɨ' tʉusauro'sen pe tʉtonpa pokon pe, apʉne pʉra tikin nan ipun pʉ'kʉ pe e'nɨ'nokon wenai.\x - \xo 4:25 \xt Sakaraya 8:16\x*
\v 26 “Asakorooi kon yau kamakoitatʉu.”\f + \fr 4:26 \ft Eren 4:4 (LXX)\f* Wʉi enu u'tɨ tane ke'tʉu ausakorotasa' kon nɨ marɨ e'tane,
\v 27 mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ makoi pʉta yen oton kʉ'ku'tʉu.
\v 28 Kʉrɨ ama' pe iye'pɨ'sa' rʉ'pʉ kʉse'nin ama' pe mɨrɨ enta', e'tane tɨwɨ ne'tʉrawasomai, ɨ'rɨ rɨ kupʉ pɨ' nesii temiyatʉ ke, kamoro entu'ma' na'ne' nan repanin pe te'to' pe.
\p 
\v 29 Ɨri rɨ usauro'nɨto' kʉsepa'kanin anta kon apai, e'tane wakʉ pika'tɨnin nɨken tʉron kon ka'nin pe i'se to' e'to' awɨrɨ, kamoro etanin nan epika'tɨto' pe.
\v 30 Mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Wakʉ Papa A'kwarʉ kʉ'pokoitanʉ'tʉu aya'si'sa' kon na'ne' ike ɨye'mato' kon weyu pona rɨ.
\v 31 Ɨri pe ɨtonpa kon pɨ' ɨwe'to' kon inonkatɨ', ewe'toi'pɨ'to' kon, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ sakoro, e'sa'morʉpɨ'nɨto' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨri pe ka'pon pɨ' usauro'nɨto', tanporon nɨ ɨri pe e'pai e'nɨto' pokon pe rɨ.
\v 32 Mannʉ' pe e'tɨ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ aiko tawon pe ɨtonpa kon pɨ', ɨsentu'kena' pe ɨtonpa kon pɨ', Kʉrai yau Papa usentu'masa' ɨpɨ'nokon na'ne' kasa.\x - \xo 4:32 \xt Koro'se 3:13\x*
\c 5
\p 
\v 1 Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨ', Papa kasa te'san pe e'tɨ', ini'nʉnkanʉ ton imunkɨ pe,
\v 2 mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉuko'mansan pe usi'nʉnkan nɨto' yau, Kʉrai uya ui'nʉnkasa' kon na'ne' kasa, mɨrɨpan e'nonka'pʉ uiwano' kon pe a'po'nan tʉtʉsen mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ use'man nɨto' Papa ena' pe.\x - \xo 5:2 \xt E'sotas 29:18; Eren 40:6\x*
\p 
\v 3 E'tane ɨ'koro'tau'nokon ekuman eseru rɨ kʉse'se'sa'pɨ'nin, mɨrɨ pe pʉra ɨri rɨ, mɨrɨ pe pʉra mentai e'nɨto', apʉne pʉra serɨ ton esi ipoken pʉra rɨ wakʉ ton Papa munkɨ amʉ' iwano' pe.
\v 4 Mɨrɨ pe pʉra ɨri pe rɨ usauro'nɨto', iya'kwarʉ pʉra rɨ usauro'nɨto' mɨrɨ pe pʉra ɨri pe te'sen main apurɨto', ipokena' pen nɨ, e'tane tenki tato' rɨken imaimu pe.
\v 5 Serɨ pɨ' i'nai rɨ e'tɨ': tekumasan, mɨrɨ pe pʉra ɨri kupʉ pɨ' te'san, mɨrɨ pe pʉra mentaino kon—esi ika'sa' apurɨpɨ'nin pe—esi pʉra iyesi Kʉrai mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Papa e'to' esa' wannɨ pe\f + \fr 5:5 \fq esi pʉra iyesi Kʉrai mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Papa e'to' esa' wannɨ pe; \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra, \fq esi pʉra iyesi Kʉrai e'to' esa' wannɨ pe mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Papa\f* epoton kon pe pʉra rɨ.
\v 6 Ɨnʉ' rɨ ɨyenku'tɨtɨ'nin itenpʉ'pʉ rɨ main ke, apʉne pʉra mɨrɨ warai'nan pona Papa uya kota'man nɨto' uyepʉ main awɨron kon pen pona.
\v 7 Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨ', to' tonpa pe ke'tʉu.
\p 
\v 8 Apʉne pʉra ɨmɨrɨ'nokon nɨ nɨrɨ esi'pʉ ewarupɨ pe, e'tane nin si Itepuru yau iweyu pe ɨwesi kon. Ɨko'mantɨ' iweyu munkɨ pe,
\v 9 (apʉne pʉra iweyu\f + \fr 5:9 \fq iweyu, \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra \fq iya'kwarʉ\f* eperu pe e'nɨ esi tanporo wakʉ pe e'nɨto' yau, ipoken e'nɨto' yau mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ i'nairon yau)
\v 10 mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Itepuru pori'manin anwarinpatɨ'.
\v 11 Teperu kenan pen nɨ ewarupɨ tʉrawasooi kʉsa'pɨ'pɨ'tʉu, e'tane ru'ku enpoikatɨ'.
\v 12 Apʉne pʉra piyɨ'nʉ' rɨ iyesi ama'ai iku'sa' rʉ'pʉ e'sesa'pɨtʉ yau.
\v 13 E'tane tanporon nɨ isenpoikasa' iweyu ke ena tensen pe,
\v 14 apʉne pʉra iweyu esi tanporon nɨ ku'nin pe tensen pe. Mɨrɨ wenai tasa' iya:
\q1 “Aiko te'nʉnsen, apakakɨ,
\q2 eri'nɨsa' apai e'mʉ'sa'ka',
\q1 Kʉrai uya ɨwei'tɨto' pe,”
\m ta iya.
\p 
\v 15 Ti'tui' ɨko'mantɨ'—pu'pʉra pen e'tane pu'kena' pe,
\v 16 wakʉ pe ɨweyu kon apurɨtɨ', apʉne pʉra wʉi ton man ɨri pe rɨ.\x - \xo 5:16 \xt Koro'se 4:5\x*
\v 17 Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨ', iya'kwarʉ pʉra ke'tʉu, e'tane Itepuru eseru tʉto'ka'nʉ'se.
\v 18 Waain pɨ' ke'taripatʉu, miyarɨ rɨ tʉuse'se'tɨi' pʉra rɨ e'pai ɨkupʉ iya 'nokon esi. E'tane ru'ku, Iya'kwarʉ ke atarʉ'tɨtɨ'.
\v 19 Eren yai ɨtonpa kon auro'katɨ', ɨpʉreman eremu mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ iya'kwarʉ pe te'sen eren yai. Ɨserenkatɨ' ɨyewan kon apai Itepuru pɨ',
\v 20 tɨwɨrɨ rɨ tenki tawon pe e'tɨ' Papa, Ikʉipʉnʉ pɨ' tanporon pɨ' rɨ, uyepuru kon Sises Kʉrai ese' yau.\x - \xo 5:20 \xt Koro'se 3:16-17\x*
\p 
\v 21 Ɨsiyena' te'tʉse e'tɨ', Kʉrai nama auya'nokon pe rɨ.
\s1 No'pʉ Ton Mɨrɨ Awonsi'kɨ Taan'pʉ Ton
\p 
\v 22 No'pʉ ton, ataan'pʉ kon ena' e'tʉtɨ' Itepuru ena' ɨye'tʉrʉ kon pe rɨ.\x - \xo 5:22 \xt Koro'se 3:18; 1 Pi'ta 3:1\x*
\v 23 Apʉne pʉra taan'pʉ esi no'pʉ i'pai pe, Kʉrai esi kasa so'si i'pai pe, tʉpun, ipika'tɨnin pe te'to'.
\v 24 So'si ne'tʉyai'ne' kasa Kʉrai ena', mɨrɨ kasa no'pʉ ton e'tʉto' pe iyesi tʉtaan'pʉ kon ena' tanporon yau rɨ.
\p 
\v 25 Taan'pʉ ton, ɨno'pʉ kon i'nʉnkatɨ', Kʉrai uya so'si i'nʉnkasa' na'ne' kasa, te'nonkai' itiwano' pe,\x - \xo 5:25 \xt Koro'se 3:19; 1 Pi'ta 3:7\x*
\v 26 wakʉ pe iku'nin pe, ikorʉka tʉuya winɨ\f + \fr 5:26 \fq ikorʉka tʉuya winɨ; \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra, \fq ikorʉkasa' tʉuya winɨ\f* tuna ke tʉmaimu winɨ,
\v 27 itʉto' pe tʉuya tena' rɨ enkena' so'si pe rɨ, ita'si'sa' pe pʉra rɨ, mɨrɨ pe pʉra itepikɨrɨi pʉra rɨ, mɨrɨ pe pʉra ɨ'rɨ rɨ ima'takʉʉi pʉra rɨ, e'tane wakʉ pe, imaku'pɨ pe pʉra.
\v 28 Mɨrɨ na'ne' kasa, taan'pʉ ton uya tʉno'pʉ kon i'nʉnkato' pe iyesi tʉpun kon i'nʉnka tʉuya'nokon pe rɨ. Kʉrɨ tʉno'pʉ i'nʉnkanin usi'nʉnka rɨ mɨrɨ.
\v 29 Ɨnʉ' ken tʉpun ewaruma'tɨnin, e'tane ewekʉ iya mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ imainanpa iya, so'si ku'ai'ne' Kʉrai kasa—
\v 30 apʉne pʉra ipun pʉ'kʉ pe e'nɨ pɨ'.
\v 31 “Mɨrɨ wenai, warawo' uya tʉkʉipʉnʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉsan nɨnto' pe iyesi, mɨrɨpan ena tʉno'pʉ ya' tikin nɨ, mɨrɨpan kon ena tikin nɨ ipun,”\f + \fr 5:31 \ft Iseneses 2:24\f* tasa'.
\v 32 Serɨ serɨ eke kuru ama'aino—e'tane usaurokʉ serɨ Kʉrai mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ so'si pɨ'.
\v 33 Mɨrɨ nin si e'tane, akaisarɨ'nokon kuru ɨno'pʉ kon i'nʉnkato' auya'nokon pe iyesi mɨsi'nʉnkayatʉi'ne' kasa, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ no'pʉ uya tʉtaan'pʉ namato' pe iyesi.
\c 6
\s1 Mʉre Amʉ' Mɨrɨ Awonsi'kɨ To' Sanon
\p 
\v 1 Mʉre amʉ', asanon kon maimu awɨrɨ e'tɨ' Itepuru yau, apʉne pʉra serɨ esi ipokena' pe.\x - \xo 6:1 \xt Koro'se 3:20\x*
\v 2 “Ɨkʉipʉnʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ asan inamakɨ”—wapiyaro' rɨ apiyontɨn nɨto' ikupʉ uya tukai' usauro'nɨsa' itonpa—
\v 3 “wakʉ pe ɨwesi pa inke ɨuko'mamʉ pa serɨ non po,”\f + \fr 6:3 \ft Isu'taronomi 5:16\f* tawon.
\v 4 Ikʉipʉnʉ ton, ɨmunkɨ kon tʉsakoropai' pʉra e'tɨ'; e'tane ru'ku, to' emo'katɨ' Itepuru eseru yau to' tenupai' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ to' tauro'kai'.\x - \xo 6:4 \xt Koro'se 3:21\x*
\s1 Apiyo' Ton Mɨrɨ Awonsi'kɨ Epuru Ton
\p 
\v 5 Apiyo' ton, non pon kon ɨyepuru kon maimu awɨrɨ e'tɨ', to' nama pe mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tenari'nʉnse to' pɨ', wakʉ pe itewan, Kʉrai maimu awɨrɨ ɨwesi kon pe rɨ.\x - \xo 6:5 \xt Koro'se 3:22-25\x*
\v 6 To' maimu awɨrɨ e'tɨ', to' uya ɨyenpɨ'tane'nokon nɨken pen wakʉ tato' pe to' uya ɨpɨ'nokon, e'tane Kʉrai apiyo' ton pe, Papa eseru kupʉ pɨ' ɨyewan kon apai.
\v 7 Iyapiyo' pe e'tɨ' ari'kena' pe, Itepuru apiyo' pe ɨwesi kon pe, ka'pon amʉ' pen,
\v 8 apʉne pʉra i'tu auya'nokon Itepuru uya tanporon kon e'ma wakʉ inkuu'pʉ pɨ', poitorʉ pe te'sen mɨrɨ pe pʉra ɨnʉ' enawon pen nɨ.
\p 
\v 9 Mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ esanon, ayapiyo' kon iku'tɨ' mɨrɨ kasa rɨ marɨ. To' kʉsenari'patʉu, i'tu auya'nokon ke kʉrɨ asa'rɨ rɨ ɨyepuru kon mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ to' epuru esi Epʉn pon, tenu yawon kenan pen nɨ nin.\x - \xo 6:9 \xt Isu'taronomi 10:17; Koro'se 3:25; 4:1\x*
\s1 Papa Amataai
\p 
\v 10 Iu'matʉ pe, pana' pe e'tɨ' Itepuru yau mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ meruntɨ ipana'pano yau.
\v 11 Tanporo kuru Papa amataai ya' enatɨ', wakʉ pe ɨye'soto'ka kon pa makoi eseru namai'.
\v 12 Apʉne pʉra pun pokon pe mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ mʉn pokon pe e'suranman pɨ' e'nɨ'nokon pen, e'tane esanon mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ eke ton, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ serɨ ewarupɨ orʉ meruntɨrʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨri a'kwarʉ ton pana'pano, ka' eseru yawon kon pokon pe nin e'suranman.
\v 13 Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨ', tanporo Papa amataai ya' enatɨ', ɨri weyu e'seposa' a'tai, wakʉ pe ɨye'soto'ka kon pa, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tanporon nɨ kupʉ tʉpo, ɨye'soto'ka kon pa.
\v 14 Pana' pe e'soto'katɨ' i'nairon ɨpokʉrʉʉi kon pe ɨworo'pai kon oi, ipoken e'nɨto' ɨpɨtɨ kon wapu pe,\x - \xo 6:14 \xt Aisaya 11:5; 59:17\x*
\v 15 a'ta kon temaikai' tʉusewankamai' pʉra e'nɨto' wakʉ ekareei ya' wakʉ pe iye'kamasa' pe.\x - \xo 6:15 \xt Aisaya 52:7\x*
\v 16 Serɨ tonpa ton pe apurɨto' anʉntɨ' awapu kon pe, serɨ ke tanporon ɨri pʉre ton i'nɨ'panʉkʉ kon pa.
\v 17 Epika'tɨn nɨto' anʉntɨ' ayarʉkooi kon pe mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨsuparaai kon pe Iya'kwarʉ, Papa Maimu pe te'sen.\x - \xo 6:17 \xt Aisaya 59:17\x*
\v 18 Mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨpʉrematɨ' Iya'kwarʉ yau tanporo te'ku'sen a'tai rɨ, ti'tui' pʉra rɨ ɨpʉreman nɨto' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ esa'to' yai. Serɨ itewan yau esii'ma, tenu ke esii'ma mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tɨwɨrɨ rɨ ɨpʉremai'ma tanporon kon wakʉ ton pona.
\p 
\v 19 Upona nɨrɨ ɨpʉrematɨ', unta a'koka uya a'tai, main ke urepato' pe enari'mʉra tonan tawon itekare ku'to' pe uya ti'tusen pe,
\v 20 kʉrɨ rɨ pe rɨ enno'sa' pe e'ai'ne' i'sen yau. Ɨpʉrematɨ' enari'mʉra ekamato' pe uya, e'to' awɨrɨ.
\s1 Iu'matʉ Pe Miyarɨ Tato'
\p 
\v 21 Tai'ki'kas, tonpa rʉ'kwɨ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ iyawɨron apiyo' Itepuru yau, uya tanporon nɨ ekama mɨrɨ ɨpɨ'nokon, i'tu kon pa mɨrɨ kasa esi mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨ'rɨ pɨ' esi.\x - \xo 6:21 \xt Inkupʉ'pʉ 20:4; 2 Temu'ti 4:12\x*
\v 22 Ennoko uya ɨpiya'nokon mɨrɨ pɨkɨrɨ, ina i'tu kon pa mɨrɨ kasa ina esi tukai', mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨpori'manin kon pe.\x - \xo 6:22 \xt Koro'se 4:7-8\x*
\p 
\v 23 Tʉusewankamai' pʉra e'nɨto' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ usi'nʉnkan nɨto' apurɨto' pokon pe Papa, Ikʉipʉnʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Itepuru Sises Kʉrai winon nesii utonpa kon enakan pe.
\v 24 Tɨwɨ wakʉ nonkasa' nesii kamo uyepuru kon Sises Kʉrai i'nʉnkato' to' uya usenkʉ'sa' pʉra na'ne' nan enakan pe.
